    • getSkipHours

      public List<Integer> getSkipHours()
      Get the list of hours that aggregators can skip reading the channel. The values are numbers between 0 and 23, representing times in GMT. Hour zero is the hour beginning at midnight. Aggregators may not read the channel during hours listed in the skipHours element.
      Specified by:
      getSkipHours in interface Channel
      Returns:
      list of skip hours

    • addSkipHour

      public void addSkipHour(Integer skipHour)
      Add an hour that aggregators can skip reading the channel. Valid values are numbers between 0 and 23, representing times in GMT. Hour zero is the hour beginning at midnight.
      Specified by:
      addSkipHour in interface Channel
      Parameters:
      skipHour - the hour to skip reading the channel (0-23)

    • getSkipDays

      public List<String> getSkipDays()
      Get the list of days that aggregators can skip reading the channel. The values can be Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday or Sunday. Aggregators may not read the channel during days listed in the skipDays element.
      Specified by:
      getSkipDays in interface Channel
      Returns:
      list of skip days

    • getSkipDaysAsDayOfWeek

      public List<DayOfWeek> getSkipDaysAsDayOfWeek()
      Get the list of days that aggregators can skip reading the channel as DayOfWeek enum values. The values are converted from the string representation (Monday, Tuesday, etc.) to their corresponding DayOfWeek enum values. Aggregators may not read the channel during days listed in the skipDays element.
      Specified by:
      getSkipDaysAsDayOfWeek in interface Channel
      Returns:
      list of skip days as DayOfWeek enum values
